text: The Findlay Group is a group of islands in the Canadian Arctic Archipelago in Qikiqtaaluk Region, Nunavut. This Arctic Ocean group consists of Lougheed Island, Stupart Island, Edmund Walker Island, Grosvenor Island and Patterson Island. ==Mapping== :A.Lougheed Island, :B.Stupart Island, :C.Edmund Walker Island, :D.Grosvenor Island, :E.Patterson Island, ==External links== * Findlay Group in the Atlas of Canada - Toporama; Natural Resources Canada Category:Islands of the Queen Elizabeth Islands Category:Uninhabited islands of Qikiqtaaluk Region Category:Archipelagoes of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago
